{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192374483,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdefde2ffewlu2jDGSLuZIcR","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_b3JgqXDqWvM6BbSCpZqV3443","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/html/frontend/A-05-reset-password.html"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/html/frontend/A-05-reset-password.html</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: <!DOCTYPE html>\n2: <html lang=\"en\">\n3: <head>\n4: <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n5: <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n6: <title>NestFind — Reset Password</title>\n7: <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\">\n8: <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n9: <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@iconify/iconify@2.2.1/dist/iconify.min.js\"></script>\n10: <style>\n11: *{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}\n12: body{font-family:'Inter',system-ui,sans-serif;background:#0B0F1A;color:#F1F5F9;line-height:1.6}\n13: .root{max-width:1440px;margin:0 auto}\n14: .navbar{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:16px 48px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08)}\n15: .nav-logo{font-size:24px;font-weight:700;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent}\n16: .nav-links{display:flex;gap:32px;align-items:center}\n17: .nav-links a{color:#94A3B8;text-decoration:none;font-size:14px;font-weight:500;transition:color 0.2s}\n18: .nav-links a:hover{color:#F1F5F9}\n19: .btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;border:none;transition:all 0.2s;font-family:inherit;text-decoration:none}\n20: .btn-primary{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);color:#fff;height:48px;padding:0 24px;border-radius:12px;font-size:14px}\n21: .btn-primary:hover{box-shadow:0 0 24px rgba(74,144,217,0.3);transform:translateY(-1px)}\n22: .btn-ghost{background:transparent;color:#F1F5F9;height:40px;padding:0 16px;border-radius:8px;font-size:14px}\n23: .btn-ghost:hover{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06)}\n24: .btn-secondary{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06);color:#F1F5F9;height:48px;padding:0 24px;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);font-size:14px}\n25: .btn-secondary:hover{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1)}\n26: .btn-danger{background:rgba(248,113,113,0.15);color:#F87171;height:40px;padding:0 16px;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid rgba(248,113,113,0.2);font-size:13px}\n27: .btn-danger:hover{background:rgba(248,113,113,0.25)}\n28: .card{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;padding:24px}\n29: .card:hover{box-shadow:0 0 20px rgba(74,144,217,0.15);background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06)}\n30: input[type=\"text\"],input[type=\"email\"],input[type=\"password\"],input[type=\"tel\"],textarea,select{height:48px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:10px;padding:0 16px;color:#F1F5F9;font-size:14px;font-family:inherit;outline:none;width:100%}\n31: input:focus,textarea:focus,select:focus{border-color:rgba(74,144,217,0.5);box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(74,144,217,0.1)}\n32: input::placeholder,textarea::placeholder{color:#64748B}\n33: textarea{height:auto;padding:12px 16px;resize:vertical;min-height:100px}\n34: label{display:block;font-size:13px;font-weight:500;color:#94A3B8;margin-bottom:6px}\n35: .form-group{margin-bottom:16px}\n36: .form-link{color:#4A90D9;font-size:13px;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500}\n37: .form-link:hover{color:#5BA0E9}\n38: .badge{display:inline-block;padding:2px 10px;border-radius:9999px;font-size:11px;font-weight:600}\n39: .badge-success{color:#4ADE80;box-shadow:0 0 8px rgba(74,222,128,0.3)}\n40: .badge-warning{color:#FBBF24;box-shadow:0 0 8px rgba(251,191,36,0.3)}\n41: .badge-error{color:#F87171;box-shadow:0 0 8px rgba(248,113,113,0.3)}\n42: .var-nav-bar{position:fixed;top:12px;right:12px;display:flex;gap:6px;background:rgba(8,11,20,0.9);backdrop-filter:blur(16px);padding:6px 10px;border-radius:10px;z-index:9999;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);font-size:11px;flex-wrap:wrap;max-width:95vw}\n43: .var-nav-bar a{color:#64748B;text-decoration:none;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;padding:3px 7px;border-radius:5px;transition:all 0.2s;white-space:nowrap}\n44: .var-nav-bar a.active{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);color:#fff}\n45: .var-nav-bar a:hover:not(.active){color:#F1F5F9;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06)}\n46: .var-nav-bar .sep{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);font-size:10px}\n47: .error-text{color:#F87171;font-size:12px;margin-top:4px}\n48: .divider{height:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);margin:24px 0}\n49: .auth-wrapper{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;min-height:calc(100vh - 73px);padding:24px}\n50: .auth-card{width:100%;max-width:420px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:16px;padding:40px}\n51: .auth-card h2{font-size:28px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:-0.02em}\n52: .auth-card .subtitle{color:#94A3B8;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:32px;line-height:1.5}\n53: .input-hint{font-size:12px;color:#64748B;margin-top:6px}\n54: .auth-back-link{display:block;text-align:center;color:#94A3B8;font-size:13px;text-decoration:none;margin-top:20px;font-weight:500;transition:color 0.2s}\n55: .auth-back-link:hover{color:#F1F5F9}\n56: .success-icon{width:64px;height:64px;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(74,222,128,0.1);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin:0 auto 20px;color:#4ADE80;box-shadow:0 0 24px rgba(74,222,128,0.2)}\n57: .success-message{text-align:center;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#F1F5F9;margin-bottom:8px}\n58: .success-subtitle{text-align:center;color:#94A3B8;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:24px}\n59: .hidden{display:none}\n60: </style>\n61: </head>\n62: <body>\n63: <nav class=\"var-nav-bar\">\n64: <a href=\"A-01-landing.html\">Landing</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n65: <a href=\"A-02-login.html\">Login</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n66: <a href=\"A-03-signup.html\">Signup</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n67: <a href=\"A-04-forgot-password.html\">Forgot</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n68: <a href=\"A-05-reset-password.html\" class=\"active\">Reset</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n69: <a href=\"A-06-search.html\">Search</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n70: <a href=\"A-07-detail.html\">Detail</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n71: <a href=\"A-08-favorites.html\">Favs</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n72: <a href=\"A-09-inquiries.html\">Inq</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n73: <a href=\"A-10-profile.html\">Prof</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n74: <a href=\"A-11-admin-login.html\">AdLog</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n75: <a href=\"A-12-admin-dashboard.html\">AdDash</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n76: <a href=\"A-13-admin-properties.html\">AdProp</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n77: <a href=\"A-14-admin-property-form.html\">AdForm</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n78: <a href=\"A-15-admin-inquiries.html\">AdInq</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n79: <a href=\"A-16-admin-users.html\">AdUsr</a>\n80: </nav>\n81: <div class=\"root\">\n82: <nav class=\"navbar\">\n83:   <div class=\"nav-logo\">NestFind</div>\n84:   <div class=\"nav-links\">\n85:     <a href=\"A-06-search.html\">Browse</a>\n86:     <a href=\"A-01-landing.html\">Home</a>\n87:   </div>\n88: </nav>\n89: <div class=\"auth-wrapper\">\n90:   <!-- Form view -->\n91:   <div class=\"auth-card\" id=\"reset-form-view\">\n92:     <h2>Set new password</h2>\n93:     <p class=\"subtitle\">Choose a strong password for your account</p>\n94: \n95:     <div class=\"form-group\">\n96:       <label for=\"new-password\">New Password</label>\n97:       <input type=\"password\" id=\"new-password\" placeholder=\"Enter new password\">\n98:       <p class=\"input-hint\">At least 8 characters</p>\n99:     </div>\n100: \n101:     <div class=\"form-group\">\n102:       <label for=\"confirm-new-password\">Confirm New Password</label>\n103:       <input type=\"password\" id=\"confirm-new-password\" placeholder=\"Re-enter new password\">\n104:     </div>\n105: \n106:     <button type=\"submit\" class=\"btn btn-primary\" style=\"width:100%\">Reset Password</button>\n107:   </div>\n108: \n109:   <!-- Success view (hidden by default) -->\n110:   <div class=\"auth-card hidden\" id=\"reset-success-view\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n111:     <div class=\"success-icon\">\n112:       <iconify-icon icon=\"mdi:check\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\"></iconify-icon>\n113:     </div>\n114:     <h2 style=\"text-align:center\">Password reset successful!</h2>\n115:     <p class=\"subtitle\" style=\"text-align:center\">Your password has been updated. You can now sign in with your new password.</p>\n116: \n117:     <a href=\"A-02-login.html\" class=\"btn btn-primary\" style=\"width:100%;text-decoration:none\">Back to Sign In</a>\n118:   </div>\n119: </div>\n120: </div>\n121: </body>\n122: </html>\n\n(End of file - total 122 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n<title>NestFind — Reset Password</title>\n<link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\">\n<link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@iconify/iconify@2.2.1/dist/iconify.min.js\"></script>\n<style>\n*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}\nbody{font-family:'Inter',system-ui,sans-serif;background:#0B0F1A;color:#F1F5F9;line-height:1.6}\n.root{max-width:1440px;margin:0 auto}\n.navbar{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:16px 48px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08)}\n.nav-logo{font-size:24px;font-weight:700;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent}\n.nav-links{display:flex;gap:32px;align-items:center}\n.nav-links a{color:#94A3B8;text-decoration:none;font-size:14px;font-weight:500;transition:color 0.2s}\n.nav-links a:hover{color:#F1F5F9}\n.btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;border:none;transition:all 0.2s;font-family:inherit;text-decoration:none}\n.btn-primary{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);color:#fff;height:48px;padding:0 24px;border-radius:12px;font-size:14px}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/design/html/frontend/A-05-reset-password.html","time":{"start":1779192374196,"end":1779192374482}},"id":"prt_e40211d9f001e2EJoD7vk1BHJF","sessionID":"ses_1bfdefde2ffewlu2jDGSLuZIcR","messageID":"msg_e402105d3001nwN5OufPHc7Exa"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192376298,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdefde2ffewlu2jDGSLuZIcR","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_vm4uZJ0itXfBrQ4heRTU1755","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Component Patterns\n2: \n3: Modern component architecture using Shadcn/UI, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## Function Component Pattern (PREFERRED)\n8: \n9: ### Why Function Components\n10: \n11: All components use function components with TypeScript for:\n12: \n13: - Explicit type safety for props\n14: - Consistent component signatures\n15: - Clear prop interface documentation\n16: - Better IDE autocomplete\n17: \n18: ### Basic Pattern\n19: \n20: ```typescript\n21: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n22: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n23: \n24: interface MyComponentProps {\n25:   /** User ID to display */\n26:   userId: number;\n27:   /** Optional callback when action occurs */\n28:   onAction?: () => void;\n29: }\n30: \n31: export default function MyComponent({ userId, onAction }: MyComponentProps) {\n32:   return (\n33:     <div className=\"p-4\">\n34:       User: {userId}\n35:       <Button onClick={onAction}>Action</Button>\n36:     </div>\n37:   );\n38: }\n39: ```\n40: \n41: **Key Points:**\n42: \n43: - Props interface defined separately with JSDoc comments\n44: - Destructure props in parameters\n45: - Default export at bottom\n46: - Use Tailwind classes for styling\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Shadcn/UI Component Usage\n51: \n52: ### Available Components\n53: \n54: Shadcn/UI components are in `~/components/ui/`:\n55: \n56: ```typescript\n57: // Buttons\n58: import { Button, buttonVariants } from '~/components/ui/button';\n59: \n60: // Forms\n61: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n62: import { Label } from '~/components/ui/label';\n63: import {\n64:   Form,\n65:   FormControl,\n66:   FormField,\n67:   FormItem,\n68:   FormLabel,\n69:   FormMessage,\n70: } from '~/components/ui/form';\n71: \n72: // Cards\n73: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '~/components/ui/card';\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### Button Component\n77: \n78: ```typescript\n79: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n80: \n81: // Variants\n82: <Button variant=\"default\">Primary</Button>\n83: <Button variant=\"secondary\">Secondary</Button>\n84: <Button variant=\"destructive\">Delete</Button>\n85: <Button variant=\"outline\">Outlined</Button>\n86: <Button variant=\"ghost\">Ghost</Button>\n87: <Button variant=\"link\">Link</Button>\n88: \n89: // Sizes\n90: <Button size=\"sm\">Small</Button>\n91: <Button size=\"default\">Default</Button>\n92: <Button size=\"lg\">Large</Button>\n93: <Button size=\"icon\"><Icon /></Button>\n94: \n95: // States\n96: <Button disabled>Disabled</Button>\n97: <Button className=\"w-full\">Full Width</Button>\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Card Component\n101: \n102: ```typescript\n103: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '~/components/ui/card';\n104: \n105: <Card className=\"w-full max-w-md\">\n106:   <CardHeader>\n107:     <CardTitle>Card Title</CardTitle>\n108:   </CardHeader>\n109:   <CardContent className=\"space-y-4\">\n110:     <p>Card content goes here</p>\n111:   </CardContent>\n112: </Card>\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Form Components (MANDATORY PATTERN — all forms must use this)\n116: \n117: ```typescript\n118: import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';\n119: import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';\n120: import { z } from 'zod';\n121: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n122: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n123: import {\n124:   Form,\n125:   FormControl,\n126:   FormField,\n127:   FormItem,\n128:   FormLabel,\n129:   FormMessage,\n130: } from '~/components/ui/form';\n131: \n132: const schema = z.object({\n133:   email: z.string().email(),\n134:   password: z.string().min(6),\n135: });\n136: \n137: type FormData = z.infer<typeof schema>;\n138: \n139: export default function LoginForm() {\n140:   const form = useForm<FormData>({\n141:     resolver: zodResolver(schema),\n142:     defaultValues: { email: '', password: '' },\n143:   });\n144: \n145:   return (\n146:     <Form {...form}>\n147:       <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)} className=\"space-y-4\">\n148:         <FormField\n149:           control={form.control}\n150:           name=\"email\"\n151:           render={({ field }) => (\n152:             <FormItem>\n153:               <FormLabel>Email</FormLabel>\n154:               <FormControl>\n155:                 <Input placeholder=\"Enter email\" {...field} />\n156:               </FormControl>\n157:               <FormMessage />\n158:             </FormItem>\n159:           )}\n160:         />\n161:         <Button type=\"submit\">Submit</Button>\n162:       </form>\n163:     </Form>\n164:   );\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## CVA (Class Variance Authority)\n171: \n172: ### What is CVA\n173: \n174: CVA is used for component variants in Shadcn/UI. It creates type-safe variant props.\n175: \n176: ### Example from Button Component\n177: \n178: ```typescript\n179: import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';\n180: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n181: \n182: const buttonVariants = cva(\n183:   // Base styles applied to all buttons\n184:   'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md text-sm font-medium transition-all',\n185:   {\n186:     variants: {\n187:       variant: {\n188:         default: 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90',\n189:         destructive: 'bg-destructive text-white hover:bg-destructive/90',\n190:         outline: 'border bg-background hover:bg-accent',\n191:         secondary: 'bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80',\n192:         ghost: 'hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground',\n193:         link: 'text-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline',\n194:       },\n195:       size: {\n196:         default: 'h-9 px-4 py-2',\n197:         sm: 'h-8 px-3',\n198:         lg: 'h-10 px-6',\n199:         icon: 'size-9',\n200:       },\n201:     },\n202:     defaultVariants: {\n203:       variant: 'default',\n204:       size: 'default',\n205:     },\n206:   }\n207: );\n208: \n209: // Usage in component\n210: function Button({\n211:   className,\n212:   variant,\n213:   size,\n214:   ...props\n215: }: React.ComponentProps<'button'> & VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants>) {\n216:   return (\n217:     <button\n218:       className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size, className }))}\n219:       {...props}\n220:     />\n221:   );\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## When to Add a Variant vs Use className (MANDATORY)\n228: \n229: All reusable components must follow these rules:\n230: \n231: 1. **Every reusable component MUST accept a `className` prop** — this allows call-site-specific layout overrides\n232: 2. **Add a cva variant when:**\n233:    - The style combination appears at 2+ call sites\n234:    - It represents a semantic state (error, success, warning, loading, ghost, compact)\n235:    - It changes the visual identity of the component (not just layout)\n236: 3. **Use `className` when:**\n237:    - The override is context-specific and used at only 1 call site\n238:    - It's a layout concern (width, height, padding offset, positioning)\n239:    - It's a dynamic value passed from props (e.g., `className={style.text}`)\n240: \n241: ```typescript\n242: // ✅ CORRECT — Semantic state as variant\n243: <Input variant=\"error\" />\n244: \n245: // ✅ CORRECT — One-off layout as className\n246: <Input className=\"pl-10\" />\n247: \n248: // ❌ WRONG — Duplicated error classes at call sites\n249: <Input className=\"border-red-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-red-500/20\" />\n250: \n251: // ❌ WRONG — Creating a new component for a style difference\n252: // Instead, add a variant to the existing component\n253: ```\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## cn() Utility for Class Merging\n258: \n259: ### What is cn()\n260: \n261: `cn()` combines `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` for conditional class merging:\n262: \n263: ```typescript\n264: // ~/lib/utils.ts\n265: import { clsx, type ClassValue } from 'clsx';\n266: import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';\n267: \n268: export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {\n269:   return twMerge(clsx(inputs));\n270: }\n271: ```\n272: \n273: ### Usage Examples\n274: \n275: ```typescript\n276: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n277: \n278: // Conditional classes\n279: <div className={cn(\n280:   'p-4 bg-background',\n281:   isActive && 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground',\n282:   isDisabled && 'opacity-50 pointer-events-none'\n283: )} />\n284: \n285: // Merging with overrides\n286: <Button className={cn(\n287:   buttonVariants({ variant: 'default' }),\n288:   'w-full' // Override width\n289: )} />\n290: \n291: // Array of conditions\n292: <div className={cn([\n293:   'base-class',\n294:   condition1 && 'class-1',\n295:   condition2 && 'class-2',\n296: ])} />\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ---\n300: \n301: ## asChild Pattern (Radix UI)\n302: \n303: ### What is asChild\n304: \n305: The `asChild` prop allows composing components with custom elements:\n306: \n307: ```typescript\n308: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n309: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n310: \n311: // Button as Link\n312: <Button asChild>\n313:   <Link to=\"/dashboard\">Go to Dashboard</Link>\n314: </Button>\n315: \n316: // Button as anchor\n317: <Button asChild variant=\"link\">\n318:   <a href=\"https://example.com\">External Link</a>\n319: </Button>\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### How it Works\n323: \n324: The Button uses Radix's `Slot` component:\n325: \n326: ```typescript\n327: import { Slot } from '@radix-ui/react-slot';\n328: \n329: function Button({ asChild = false, ...props }) {\n330:   const Comp = asChild ? Slot : 'button';\n331:   return <Comp {...props} />;\n332: }\n333: ```\n334: \n335: ### IMPORTANT: asChild + Link Anti-Pattern\n336: \n337: **NEVER use `asChild` with `Link` inside `DropdownMenuItem`:**\n338: \n339: ```typescript\n340: // ❌ CAUSES VISUAL \"BLINK\" ON FIRST RENDER\n341: <DropdownMenuItem asChild>\n342:   <Link to={`/dashboard/users/${user.id}`}>\n343:     <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />\n344:     View Details\n345:   </Link>\n346: </DropdownMenuItem>\n347: \n348: // ✅ USE onClick with navigate() INSTEAD\n349: <DropdownMenuItem onClick={() => navigate(`/dashboard/users/${user.id}`)}>\n350:   <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />\n351:   View Details\n352: </DropdownMenuItem>\n353: ```\n354: \n355: **Better: Use the ActionMenu Component**\n356: \n357: For table action menus, use the reusable `ActionMenu` component:\n358: \n359: ```typescript\n360: import { ActionMenu } from '~/components/ui/action-menu';\n361: \n362: <ActionMenu\n363:   items={[\n364:     {\n365:       label: 'View Details',\n366:       icon: <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />,\n367:       href: `/dashboard/users/${user.id}`,  // Uses navigate() internally\n368:     },\n369:     {\n370:       label: 'Delete',\n371:       icon: <Trash2 className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />,\n372:       onClick: () => handleDelete(user.id),\n373:       variant: 'destructive',\n374:     },\n375:   ]}\n376: />\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Component Structure Template\n382: \n383: ### Recommended Order\n384: \n385: ```typescript\n386: import { useState, useCallback, useMemo, useEffect } from 'react';\n387: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n388: \n389: // Redux\n390: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from '~/redux/store/hooks';\n391: \n392: // UI Components\n393: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n394: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader } from '~/components/ui/card';\n395: \n396: // Utilities\n397: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n398: \n399: // Types\n400: import type { User } from '~/types/user';\n401: \n402: // 1. PROPS INTERFACE (with JSDoc)\n403: interface MyComponentProps {\n404:   /** The ID of the entity to display */\n405:   entityId: number;\n406:   /** Optional callback when action completes */\n407:   onComplete?: () => void;\n408:   /** Display mode */\n409:   mode?: 'view' | 'edit';\n410: }\n411: \n412: // 2. COMPONENT DEFINITION\n413: export default function MyComponent({\n414:   entityId,\n415:   onComplete,\n416:   mode = 'view',\n417: }: MyComponentProps) {\n418:   // 3. HOOKS (in this order)\n419:   // - Redux hooks\n420:   const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n421:   const user = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.currentUser);\n422:   const loading = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.loading);\n423: \n424:   // - Local state\n425:   const [selectedItem, setSelectedItem] = useState<string | null>(null);\n426:   const [isEditing, setIsEditing] = useState(mode === 'edit');\n427: \n428:   // - Memoized values\n429:   const filteredData = useMemo(() => {\n430:     return data.filter((item) => item.active);\n431:   }, [data]);\n432: \n433:   // - Effects\n434:   useEffect(() => {\n435:     // Setup\n436:     return () => {\n437:       // Cleanup\n438:     };\n439:   }, []);\n440: \n441:   // 4. EVENT HANDLERS (with useCallback for passed handlers)\n442:   const handleItemSelect = useCallback((itemId: string) => {\n443:     setSelectedItem(itemId);\n444:   }, []);\n445: \n446:   const handleSave = useCallback(async () => {\n447:     try {\n448:       // Save logic\n449:       onComplete?.();\n450:     } catch (error) {\n451:       console.error('Failed to save:', error);\n452:     }\n453:   }, [onComplete]);\n454: \n455:   // 5. RENDER\n456:   return (\n457:     <Card className=\"w-full max-w-md\">\n458:       <CardHeader>\n459:         <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold\">My Component</h2>\n460:       </CardHeader>\n461:       <CardContent className=\"space-y-4\">\n462:         <p className={cn('text-muted-foreground', loading && 'opacity-50')}>\n463:           {user?.email}\n464:         </p>\n465:         <Button onClick={handleSave} disabled={loading}>\n466:           {loading ? 'Loading...' : 'Save'}\n467:         </Button>\n468:       </CardContent>\n469:     </Card>\n470:   );\n471: }\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ---\n475: \n476: ## Component Separation\n477: \n478: ### When to Split Components\n479: \n480: **Split into multiple components when:**\n481: \n482: - Component exceeds 200 lines\n483: - Multiple distinct responsibilities\n484: - Reusable sections\n485: - Complex nested JSX\n486: \n487: **Example:**\n488: \n489: ```typescript\n490: // ❌ AVOID - Monolithic\n491: function MassivePage() {\n492:   // 500+ lines\n493:   // Header logic\n494:   // Form logic\n495:   // Table logic\n496:   // Modal logic\n497: }\n498: \n499: // ✅ PREFERRED - Modular\n500: function Page() {\n501:   return (\n502:     <div className=\"space-y-6\">\n503:       <PageHeader />\n504:       <SearchForm onSearch={handleSearch} />\n505:       <DataTable data={filteredData} />\n506:       <ActionModal open={isOpen} onClose={handleClose} />\n507:     </div>\n508:   );\n509: }\n510: ```\n511: \n512: ### When to Keep Together\n513: \n514: **Keep in same file when:**\n515: \n516: - Component < 100 lines\n517: - Tightly coupled logic\n518: - Not reusable elsewhere\n519: - Simple presentation component\n520: \n521: ---\n522: \n523: ## Lazy Loading Pattern\n524: \n525: ### When to Lazy Load\n526: \n527: Lazy load components that are:\n528: \n529: - Heavy (DataGrid, charts, rich text editors)\n530: - Route-level components\n531: - Modal/dialog content (not shown initially)\n532: - Below-the-fold content\n533: \n534: ### How to Lazy Load\n535: \n536: ```typescript\n537: import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';\n538: \n539: // Lazy load heavy component\n540: const HeavyEditor = lazy(() => import('./HeavyEditor'));\n541: \n542: // Usage with Suspense\n543: function Page() {\n544:   return (\n545:     <Suspense fallback={<div>Loading...</div>}>\n546:       <HeavyEditor />\n547:     </Suspense>\n548:   );\n549: }\n550: ```\n551: \n552: ---\n553: \n554: ## Component Communication\n555: \n556: ### Props Down, Events Up\n557: \n558: ```typescript\n559: // Parent\n560: function Parent() {\n561:   const [selectedId, setSelectedId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n562: \n563:   return (\n564:     <Child\n565:       data={data} // Props down\n566:       onSelect={setSelectedId} // Events up\n567:     />\n568:   );\n569: }\n570: \n571: // Child\n572: interface ChildProps {\n573:   data: Data[];\n574:   onSelect: (id: string) => void;\n575: }\n576: \n577: export default function Child({ data, onSelect }: ChildProps) {\n578:   return (\n579:     <ul>\n580:       {data.map((item) => (\n581:         <li key={item.id} onClick={() => onSelect(item.id)}>\n582:           {item.name}\n583:         </li>\n584:       ))}\n585:     </ul>\n586:   );\n587: }\n588: ```\n589: \n590: ### Using Redux for Shared State\n591: \n592: ```typescript\n593: // When state needs to be shared across components\n594: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from '~/redux/store/hooks';\n595: import { selectItem } from '~/redux/features/itemSlice';\n596: \n597: function Child() {\n598:   const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n599:   const selectedId = useAppSelector((state) => state.item.selectedId);\n600: \n601:   const handleSelect = (id: string) => {\n602:     dispatch(selectItem(id));\n603:   };\n604: \n605:   return <div onClick={() => handleSelect('123')}>Select</div>;\n606: }\n607: ```\n608: \n609: ---\n610: \n611: ## Summary\n612: \n613: **Modern Component Recipe:**\n614: \n615: 1. Function components with TypeScript props interface\n616: 2. Shadcn/UI components from `~/components/ui/`\n617: 3. `cn()` utility for conditional classes\n618: 4. Tailwind CSS for styling\n619: 5. `useAppSelector` and `useAppDispatch` for Redux\n620: 6. Event handlers with `useCallback` when passed to children\n621: 7. Default export at bottom\n622: \n623: ---\n624: \n625: ## MANDATORY: Async State Handling\n626: \n627: Every component that fetches data MUST handle all three states:\n628: \n629: ```typescript\n630: // MANDATORY: Loading state\n631: if (isLoading) return <LoadingSkeleton />;\n632: \n633: // MANDATORY: Error state\n634: if (error) return <ErrorState message={error.message} onRetry={refetch} />;\n635: \n636: // MANDATORY: Empty state (distinct from error)\n637: if (!data?.length) return <EmptyState title=\"No items found\" />;\n638: \n639: // Happy path\n640: return <DataList items={data} />;\n641: ```\n642: \n643: **Rules:**\n644: - Loading skeleton (not spinner) for initial data loads\n645: - Error state with retry button for API failures\n646: - Empty state for zero results (NOT the same component as error)\n647: - Error boundaries wrapping route-level components for uncaught errors\n648: \n649: ## MANDATORY: No Business Logic in Components\n650: \n651: Components must only handle rendering and event delegation:\n652: \n653: ```typescript\n654: // BAD: Business logic in component\n655: const filteredUsers = users.filter(u => u.role === 'admin' && u.isActive);\n656: const sortedUsers = filteredUsers.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));\n657: \n658: // GOOD: Logic in selector/utility\n659: const activeAdmins = useAppSelector(selectActiveAdmins);\n660: ```\n661: \n662: **See Also:**\n663: \n664: - [styling-guide.md](styling-guide.md) - Tailwind CSS patterns\n665: - [common-patterns.md](common-patterns.md) - Form patterns\n666: - [complete-examples.md](complete-examples.md) - Full working examples\n\n(End of file - total 666 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Component Patterns\n\nModern component architecture using Shadcn/UI, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript.\n\n---\n\n## Function Component Pattern (PREFERRED)\n\n### Why Function Components\n\nAll components use function components with TypeScript for:\n\n- Explicit type safety for props\n- Consistent component signatures\n- Clear prop interface documentation\n- Better IDE autocomplete\n\n### Basic Pattern\n\n```typescript","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md","time":{"start":1779192376012,"end":1779192376297}},"id":"prt_e4021253e001RbE98IAlNcnMzg","sessionID":"ses_1bfdefde2ffewlu2jDGSLuZIcR","messageID":"msg_e402105d3001nwN5OufPHc7Exa"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192378038,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdefde2ffewlu2jDGSLuZIcR","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_jcCHQSN5Do0pPVk1HZmh0822","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/common-patterns.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/common-patterns.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Common Patterns\n2: \n3: Frequently used patterns for forms, authentication, Redux state, and other common UI elements.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## MANDATORY: React Hook Form + Zod + shadcn Form (ALL forms must use this)\n8: \n9: > **Manual `useState` for form field values is FORBIDDEN. Always use `useForm` + `zodResolver` + shadcn `Form`/`FormField`/`FormItem`/`FormControl`/`FormMessage` components.**\n10: \n11: ### Form Schema with Zod\n12: \n13: Location: `~/utils/validations/{feature}.ts`\n14: \n15: ```typescript\n16: import * as z from 'zod';\n17: \n18: // Define schema\n19: export const loginSchema = z.object({\n20:   email: z.string().email('Invalid email address'),\n21:   password: z.string().min(6, 'Password must be at least 6 characters'),\n22: });\n23: \n24: // Infer TypeScript type from schema\n25: export type LoginFormData = z.infer<typeof loginSchema>;\n26: \n27: // Registration with confirmation\n28: export const registerSchema = z.object({\n29:   email: z.string().email('Invalid email address'),\n30:   password: z.string().min(6, 'Password must be at least 6 characters'),\n31:   confirmPassword: z.string(),\n32: }).refine((data) => data.password === data.confirmPassword, {\n33:   message: \"Passwords don't match\",\n34:   path: ['confirmPassword'],\n35: });\n36: \n37: export type RegisterFormData = z.infer<typeof registerSchema>;\n38: ```\n39: \n40: ### Form Component Pattern\n41: \n42: ```typescript\n43: import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';\n44: import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';\n45: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n46: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n47: import {\n48:   Form,\n49:   FormControl,\n50:   FormField,\n51:   FormItem,\n52:   FormLabel,\n53:   FormMessage,\n54: } from '~/components/ui/form';\n55: import { loginSchema, type LoginFormData } from '~/utils/validations/auth';\n56: \n57: export default function LoginForm() {\n58:   const form = useForm<LoginFormData>({\n59:     resolver: zodResolver(loginSchema),\n60:     defaultValues: {\n61:       email: '',\n62:       password: '',\n63:     },\n64:     mode: 'onChange', // Validate on change\n65:   });\n66: \n67:   const onSubmit = async (data: LoginFormData) => {\n68:     console.log('Form data:', data);\n69:     // Handle submission\n70:   };\n71: \n72:   return (\n73:     <Form {...form}>\n74:       <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)} className=\"space-y-4\">\n75:         <FormField\n76:           control={form.control}\n77:           name=\"email\"\n78:           render={({ field }) => (\n79:             <FormItem>\n80:               <FormLabel>Email</FormLabel>\n81:               <FormControl>\n82:                 <Input placeholder=\"Enter your email\" {...field} />\n83:               </FormControl>\n84:               <FormMessage />\n85:             </FormItem>\n86:           )}\n87:         />\n88: \n89:         <FormField\n90:           control={form.control}\n91:           name=\"password\"\n92:           render={({ field }) => (\n93:             <FormItem>\n94:               <FormLabel>Password</FormLabel>\n95:               <FormControl>\n96:                 <Input type=\"password\" placeholder=\"Enter password\" {...field} />\n97:               </FormControl>\n98:               <FormMessage />\n99:             </FormItem>\n100:           )}\n101:         />\n102: \n103:         <Button type=\"submit\" className=\"w-full\">\n104:           Sign In\n105:         </Button>\n106:       </form>\n107:     </Form>\n108:   );\n109: }\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ## Redux Slice Pattern\n115: \n116: ### Creating a Slice\n117: \n118: ```typescript\n119: // ~/redux/features/userSlice.ts\n120: import { createSlice, type PayloadAction } from '@reduxjs/toolkit';\n121: import { fetchUsers, createUser } from '~/services/httpServices/userService';\n122: import type { User, UserState } from '~/types/user';\n123: \n124: const initialState: UserState = {\n125:   users: [],\n126:   currentUser: null,\n127:   loading: false,\n128:   error: null,\n129: };\n130: \n131: const userSlice = createSlice({\n132:   name: 'user',\n133:   initialState,\n134:   reducers: {\n135:     // Synchronous actions\n136:     setCurrentUser: (state, action: PayloadAction<User | null>) => {\n137:       state.currentUser = action.payload;\n138:     },\n139:     clearError: (state) => {\n140:       state.error = null;\n141:     },\n142:     logout: (state) => {\n143:       state.currentUser = null;\n144:       state.users = [];\n145:     },\n146:   },\n147:   extraReducers: (builder) => {\n148:     builder\n149:       // Async thunk handling\n150:       .addCase(fetchUsers.pending, (state) => {\n151:         state.loading = true;\n152:         state.error = null;\n153:       })\n154:       .addCase(fetchUsers.fulfilled, (state, action) => {\n155:         state.loading = false;\n156:         state.users = action.payload;\n157:       })\n158:       .addCase(fetchUsers.rejected, (state, action) => {\n159:         state.loading = false;\n160:         state.error = action.payload as string;\n161:       });\n162:   },\n163: });\n164: \n165: export const { setCurrentUser, clearError, logout } = userSlice.actions;\n166: export default userSlice.reducer;\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ### Adding to Root Reducer\n170: \n171: ```typescript\n172: // ~/redux/store/rootReducer.ts\n173: import { combineReducers } from '@reduxjs/toolkit';\n174: import userReducer from '../features/userSlice';\n175: import counterReducer from '../features/counterSlice';\n176: \n177: const rootReducer = combineReducers({\n178:   user: userReducer,\n179:   counter: counterReducer,\n180: });\n181: \n182: export default rootReducer;\n183: ```\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## Typed Redux Hooks\n188: \n189: ### Hook Definitions\n190: \n191: Location: `~/redux/store/hooks.ts`\n192: \n193: ```typescript\n194: import type { TypedUseSelectorHook } from 'react-redux';\n195: import { useDispatch, useSelector } from 'react-redux';\n196: import type { RootState, AppDispatch } from './store';\n197: \n198: // Typed dispatch hook\n199: export const useAppDispatch = () => useDispatch<AppDispatch>();\n200: \n201: // Typed selector hook\n202: export const useAppSelector: TypedUseSelectorHook<RootState> = useSelector;\n203: ```\n204: \n205: ### Usage in Components\n206: \n207: ```typescript\n208: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from '~/redux/store/hooks';\n209: import { fetchUsers } from '~/services/httpServices/userService';\n210: import { logout } from '~/redux/features/userSlice';\n211: \n212: export default function UserPage() {\n213:   const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n214: \n215:   // Selecting state\n216:   const users = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.users);\n217:   const loading = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.loading);\n218:   const error = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.error);\n219: \n220:   // Dispatching async thunk\n221:   const handleFetch = () => {\n222:     dispatch(fetchUsers());\n223:   };\n224: \n225:   // Dispatching sync action\n226:   const handleLogout = () => {\n227:     dispatch(logout());\n228:   };\n229: \n230:   return (\n231:     // ...\n232:   );\n233: }\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ## Authentication Pattern\n239: \n240: For comprehensive authentication patterns including httpOnly cookies, route guards, and role-based access control, see the dedicated guides:\n241: \n242: - **[authentication.md](./authentication.md)** — Complete auth patterns (Redux/Context, 401 interceptor)\n243: - **[auth-guards.md](./auth-guards.md)** — Guard components, inline RBAC, decision matrix\n244: - **[authentication-architecture.md](./authentication-architecture.md)** — Auth flow and architecture overview\n245: \n246: ### Quick Reference: useAuth Hook\n247: \n248: ```typescript\n249: // Works with both Redux and Context implementations\n250: const { user, isAuthenticated, authChecked, isLoading } = useAuth();\n251: \n252: // Role-based conditional rendering\n253: {user?.role === RoleEnum.ADMIN && <AdminSection />}\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ### Quick Reference: Cookie-Based Auth\n257: \n258: ```typescript\n259: // Login — backend sets httpOnly cookie automatically\n260: const handleLogin = async (credentials: LoginFormData) => {\n261:   const response = await authService.login(credentials);\n262:   if (response.success && response.data) {\n263:     const authUser = mapToAuthUser(response.data.user);\n264:     dispatch(loginSuccess(authUser));\n265:     navigate(getHomeRouteForRole(authUser.role));\n266:   }\n267: };\n268: \n269: // Logout — backend clears httpOnly cookie\n270: const handleLogout = async () => {\n271:   await authService.logout();\n272:   dispatch(logout());\n273:   navigate('/login');\n274: };\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ### getHomeRouteForRole Utility\n278: \n279: ```typescript\n280: // ~/lib/utils/auth.ts\n281: export function getHomeRouteForRole(role: string): string {\n282:   const routeMap: Record<string, string> = {\n283:     admin: '/admin',\n284:     user: '/dashboard',\n285:     // Add your project's roles here\n286:   };\n287:   return routeMap[role] || '/';\n288: }\n289: ```\n290: \n291: ### Protected Layout (Inline RBAC — Recommended)\n292: \n293: ```typescript\n294: // ~/components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx\n295: const routeAccess: Record<string, string[]> = {\n296:   '/dashboard': ['admin', 'user'],\n297:   '/users': ['admin'],\n298:   // Populate from your PRD\n299: };\n300: \n301: export default function ProtectedLayout() {\n302:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked, user } = useAuth();\n303:   const location = useLocation();\n304: \n305:   if (!authChecked) return <LoadingSpinner />;\n306:   if (!isAuthenticated || !user) return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n307: \n308:   const currentPath = '/' + location.pathname.split('/').filter(Boolean)[0];\n309:   const allowedRoles = routeAccess[currentPath];\n310:   if (allowedRoles && !allowedRoles.includes(user.role)) {\n311:     return <Navigate to=\"/unauthorized\" replace />;\n312:   }\n313: \n314:   return <div className=\"flex h-screen\"><Sidebar /><Outlet /></div>;\n315: }\n316: ```\n317: \n318: > **Key pattern:** Auth + RBAC checks are **inline** in the layout. No separate guard wrapper needed.\n319: \n320: ### Role-Based Conditional Rendering\n321: \n322: ```typescript\n323: const { user } = useAuth();\n324: \n325: // Show admin-only navigation items\n326: {user?.role === RoleEnum.ADMIN && (\n327:   <NavLink to=\"/admin/users\">User Management</NavLink>\n328: )}\n329: \n330: // Show different content by role\n331: {user?.role === RoleEnum.ADMIN ? <AdminDashboard /> : <UserDashboard />}\n332: ```\n333: \n334: ---\n335: \n336: ## Server Actions with useActionState\n337: \n338: ### Server Action Definition\n339: \n340: Location: `~/utils/actions/auth.ts`\n341: \n342: ```typescript\n343: 'use server';\n344: \n345: export async function loginAction(prevState: any, formData: FormData) {\n346:   const email = formData.get('email') as string;\n347:   const password = formData.get('password') as string;\n348: \n349:   // Validate\n350:   if (!email || !password) {\n351:     return { error: JSON.stringify({ email: 'Email is required' }) };\n352:   }\n353: \n354:   try {\n355:     // Call API\n356:     const response = await fetch('/api/auth/login', {\n357:       method: 'POST',\n358:       body: JSON.stringify({ email, password }),\n359:     });\n360: \n361:     if (!response.ok) {\n362:       return { error: 'Invalid credentials' };\n363:     }\n364: \n365:     return { message: 'Login successful' };\n366:   } catch (error) {\n367:     return { error: 'An error occurred' };\n368:   }\n369: }\n370: ```\n371: \n372: ### Using useActionState\n373: \n374: ```typescript\n375: import { useEffect } from 'react';\n376: import { useActionState } from 'react';\n377: import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';\n378: import { loginAction } from '~/utils/actions/auth';\n379: import { loginSchema, type LoginFormData } from '~/utils/validations/auth';\n380: \n381: export default function LoginPage() {\n382:   const [state, formAction] = useActionState(loginAction, null);\n383: \n384:   const form = useForm<LoginFormData>({\n385:     resolver: zodResolver(loginSchema),\n386:     defaultValues: { email: '', password: '' },\n387:   });\n388: \n389:   // Handle server-side errors\n390:   useEffect(() => {\n391:     if (state?.error) {\n392:       const errors = JSON.parse(state.error);\n393:       Object.keys(errors).forEach((key) => {\n394:         form.setError(key as keyof LoginFormData, {\n395:           message: errors[key],\n396:         });\n397:       });\n398:     }\n399:   }, [state, form]);\n400: \n401:   return (\n402:     <Form {...form}>\n403:       <form action={formAction} className=\"space-y-4\">\n404:         {/* Form fields */}\n405: \n406:         {state?.error && (\n407:           <p className=\"text-sm text-destructive\">{state.error}</p>\n408:         )}\n409:         {state?.message && (\n410:           <p className=\"text-sm text-green-600\">{state.message}</p>\n411:         )}\n412: \n413:         <Button type=\"submit\">Sign In</Button>\n414:       </form>\n415:     </Form>\n416:   );\n417: }\n418: ```\n419: \n420: ---\n421: \n422: ## Conditional Rendering Patterns\n423: \n424: ### Loading State\n425: \n426: ```typescript\n427: const { loading, error, data } = useAppSelector((state) => state.feature);\n428: \n429: if (loading) {\n430:   return <LoadingSpinner />;\n431: }\n432: \n433: if (error) {\n434:   return <ErrorMessage error={error} />;\n435: }\n436: \n437: if (!data || data.length === 0) {\n438:   return <EmptyState message=\"No items found\" />;\n439: }\n440: \n441: return <DataList data={data} />;\n442: ```\n443: \n444: ### Auth-Based Rendering\n445: \n446: ```typescript\n447: const { user, isAuthenticated } = useAuth();\n448: \n449: return (\n450:   <nav>\n451:     {isAuthenticated ? (\n452:       <>\n453:         <span>Welcome, {user?.name}</span>\n454:         <Button onClick={handleLogout}>Logout</Button>\n455:       </>\n456:     ) : (\n457:       <Button asChild>\n458:         <Link to=\"/login\">Login</Link>\n459:       </Button>\n460:     )}\n461:   </nav>\n462: );\n463: ```\n464: \n465: ### Role-Based Rendering\n466: \n467: ```typescript\n468: const { user } = useAuth();\n469: \n470: return (\n471:   <div>\n472:     {/* Show admin-only sections */}\n473:     {user?.role === RoleEnum.ADMIN && (\n474:       <section>\n475:         <h2>Admin Controls</h2>\n476:         <Button onClick={handleDeleteAll}>Delete All</Button>\n477:       </section>\n478:     )}\n479: \n480:     {/* Role-specific form fields */}\n481:     {user?.role === RoleEnum.ADMIN && (\n482:       <FormField name=\"status\" control={form.control} render={({ field }) => (\n483:         <FormItem>\n484:           <FormLabel>Status</FormLabel>\n485:           <Select onValueChange={field.onChange} value={field.value}>\n486:             {/* admin-only status options */}\n487:           </Select>\n488:         </FormItem>\n489:       )} />\n490:     )}\n491:   </div>\n492: );\n493: ```\n494: \n495: ---\n496: \n497: ## Summary\n498: \n499: **Common Patterns Checklist:**\n500: \n501: - ✅ Use React Hook Form + Zod for form validation\n502: - ✅ Define Zod schemas in `utils/validations/`\n503: - ✅ Create Redux slices in `redux/features/`\n504: - ✅ Use `useAppDispatch` and `useAppSelector` hooks\n505: - ✅ Use httpOnly cookies for auth (or Context/Redux for auth state)\n506: - ✅ Use inline RBAC in ProtectedLayout for route protection\n507: - ✅ Use `useAuth()` hook for auth state access\n508: - ✅ Handle loading, error, and empty states\n509: - ✅ Use `ActionMenu` component for table action menus (avoid `asChild` + `Link` in dropdowns)\n510: \n511: **See Also:**\n512: \n513: - [data-fetching.md](data-fetching.md) - API service patterns\n514: - [loading-and-error-states.md](loading-and-error-states.md) - Error handling\n515: - [complete-examples.md](complete-examples.md) - Full working examples\n\n(End of file - total 515 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Common Patterns\n\nFrequently used patterns for forms, authentication, Redux state, and other common UI elements.\n\n---\n\n## MANDATORY: React Hook Form + Zod + shadcn Form (ALL forms must use this)\n\n> **Manual `useState` for form field values is FORBIDDEN. Always use `useForm` + `zodResolver` + shadcn `Form`/`FormField`/`FormItem`/`FormControl`/`FormMessage` components.**\n\n### Form Schema with Zod\n\nLocation: `~/utils/validations/{feature}.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport * as z from 'zod';\n\n// Define schema\nexport const loginSchema = z.object({\n  email: z.string().email('Invalid email address'),","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/common-patterns.md","time":{"start":1779192377754,"end":1779192378037}},"id":"prt_e40212c1700101krfb6x06YWnw","sessionID":"ses_1bfdefde2ffewlu2jDGSLuZIcR","messageID":"msg_e402105d3001nwN5OufPHc7Exa"}}
