{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192393302,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdefde2ffewlu2jDGSLuZIcR","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_04_bL3zfxkrLGWvjv9qXlg18558","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # i18n Architecture Guide\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: When a project requires multilingual support, use `react-i18next` for internationalization.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Setup\n10: \n11: ### 1. Install Dependencies\n12: \n13: ```bash\n14: npm install react-i18next i18next i18next-http-backend i18next-browser-languagedetector\n15: ```\n16: \n17: ### 2. Create i18n Configuration\n18: \n19: ```typescript\n20: // app/i18n.ts\n21: import i18n from 'i18next';\n22: import { initReactI18next } from 'react-i18next';\n23: import LanguageDetector from 'i18next-browser-languagedetector';\n24: import Backend from 'i18next-http-backend';\n25: \n26: i18n\n27:   .use(Backend)\n28:   .use(LanguageDetector)\n29:   .use(initReactI18next)\n30:   .init({\n31:     fallbackLng: 'en',\n32:     supportedLngs: ['en', 'ko'],\n33:     defaultNS: 'translation',\n34:     interpolation: {\n35:       escapeValue: false, // React already escapes\n36:     },\n37:     backend: {\n38:       loadPath: '/locales/{{lng}}/{{ns}}.json',\n39:     },\n40:   });\n41: \n42: export default i18n;\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ### 3. Create Locale Files\n46: \n47: ```\n48: public/\n49: └── locales/\n50:     ├── en/\n51:     │   └── translation.json\n52:     └── ko/\n53:         └── translation.json\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ```json\n57: // public/locales/en/translation.json\n58: {\n59:   \"common\": {\n60:     \"save\": \"Save\",\n61:     \"cancel\": \"Cancel\",\n62:     \"delete\": \"Delete\",\n63:     \"loading\": \"Loading...\",\n64:     \"noResults\": \"No results found\",\n65:     \"error\": \"Something went wrong\"\n66:   },\n67:   \"auth\": {\n68:     \"login\": \"Login\",\n69:     \"logout\": \"Logout\",\n70:     \"email\": \"Email\",\n71:     \"password\": \"Password\"\n72:   }\n73: }\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### 4. Initialize in Entry Point\n77: \n78: ```typescript\n79: // root.tsx\n80: import './i18n';\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## Usage in Components\n86: \n87: ### Basic Translation\n88: \n89: ```typescript\n90: import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';\n91: \n92: export const SaveButton = () => {\n93:   const { t } = useTranslation();\n94:   return <button>{t('common.save')}</button>;\n95: };\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### With Variables\n99: \n100: ```typescript\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 158. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# i18n Architecture Guide\n\n## Overview\n\nWhen a project requires multilingual support, use `react-i18next` for internationalization.\n\n---\n\n## Setup\n\n### 1. Install Dependencies\n\n```bash\nnpm install react-i18next i18next i18next-http-backend i18next-browser-languagedetector\n```\n\n### 2. Create i18n Configuration\n\n```typescript\n// app/i18n.ts","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md","time":{"start":1779192393017,"end":1779192393301}},"id":"prt_e402166750013EOH2M6mAz4TZd","sessionID":"ses_1bfdefde2ffewlu2jDGSLuZIcR","messageID":"msg_e40213987001ulUDOefMh3yUw2"}}
